works.description: A sweet tooth can cost you a lot. For those with the money to spend, the Marquis Los Cabos resort in Baja California Sur, Mexico is offering a $1,000 Popsicle. The pricey Popsicle is made from 24 ct. gold flakes and Tequilas Premium Clase Azul Ultra, which costs $1,500 a bottle. They serve the mouth-watering ice pop by the poolside on a classic plastic stick. If you are not into the sweets, Marquis Los Cabos also offers the tequila used in the Popsicle for just $500.
